---------------------------------------------------------------------------

AGPL §13 — "Remote Network Interaction" — requires that any modified version
that interacts with users over a network must make the complete source code
available to those users. NavPanchang is an offline-first app with no server
component, but because the user runs it on their own device they are
nonetheless entitled to the source. The About screen inside the app links to
the public GitHub repository where the source code is maintained.
